webhook applies\n  2. Calls callAttrMutatingHook() which:\n     - Validates dry-run constraints\n     - Calls CreateAdmissionObjects() to create AdmissionReview request\n     - Gets REST client from ClientManager\n     - Makes POST request to webhook\n     - Verifies response with VerifyAdmissionResponse()\n     - Applies JSON patches to object if provided\n     - Handles failures with failure policy (Fail or Ignore)\n  3. Updates audit annotations from webhook response\n  4. Handles errors and continues or fails based on failure policy\n\n### Validating Webhooks (Parallel)\n**staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/validating/dispatcher.go**:\n- validatingDispatcher.Dispatch(): Pre-filters webhooks first, then spawns goroutines for parallel execution\n- Pre-filtering phase:\n  1. Checks all webhooks against rules and selectors\n  2. Caches versioned attributes for each matching webhook\n- Parallel execution phase:\n  1. Uses sync.WaitGroup to run each webhook call in a goroutine\n  2. Each goroutine calls callHook() which:\n     - Creates AdmissionReview request via CreateAdmissionObjects()\n     - Makes POST request to webhook via REST client\n     - Verifies response with VerifyAdmissionResponse()\n     - Collects errors in errCh channel\n  3. Aggregates all errors: if multiple failures, returns first error (logs others)\n  4. Handles panics in webhook calls with deferred panic recovery\n\n## 4. Request/Response Handling\n\n**staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/request/admissionreview.go**:\n- CreateAdmissionObjects(): Creates AdmissionReview request and response objects\n  - Generates unique request UID\n  - Creates versioned AdmissionReview in webhook's preferred version (v1 or v1beta1)\n  - Returns request object and response object for decoding\n- VerifyAdmissionResponse(): Validates and extracts webhook response\n  - Verifies UID matches request\n  - For mutating: validates patch and patchType are provided together\n  - For validating: ensures no patch is returned\n  - Extracts audit annotations, warnings, and mutation status\n  - Returns AdmissionResponse struct with Allowed, Patch, Result fields\n\n## 5. Webhook Communication Infrastructure\n\n**staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/util/webhook/client.go**:\n- ClientManager: Manages REST clients for webhook calls\n  - Caches clients to avoid duplicate creation\n  - Handles authentication via kubeconfig\n  - Resolves webhook service URLs\n  - Manages TLS certificates\n\n**staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/util/webhook/error.go**:\n- Error types for webhook communication failures\n- ErrCallingWebhook: Wraps webhook call failures\n- ErrWebhookRejection: Wraps webhook rejection responses\n\n## Request Flow Summary\n\nMutating flow: Admit() → Dispatch() → ShouldCallHook() → mutatingDispatcher.Dispatch() → callAttrMutatingHook() → REST client → VerifyAdmissionResponse() → apply patches\n\nValidating flow: Validate() → Dispatch() → ShouldCallHook() (pre-filter) → validatingDispatcher.Dispatch() (spawn goroutines) → callHook() (parallel) → REST client → VerifyAdmissionResponse() → aggregate errors\n\nThe chain implements proper error handling with failure policies (Fail/Ignore), audit annotation collection, warning propagation, and support for dry-run requests."
